129
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:25,000
What do you really mean by energy?

130
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:27,000
Energy is mass,

131
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:29,000
E equals mc squared.

132
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:32,000
Mass is the source of gravity.

133
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:37,000
The basic thing that mass and energy do

134
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:39,000
at a very fundamental level

135
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:42,000
is that they gravitate.

136
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:44,000
So the question is,

137
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:47,000
would this energy that's stored

138
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:49,000
between these two plates here

139
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:55,000
modify both the mass of these plates,

140
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:58,000
and would it affect the gravitation

141
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:01,000
of some other object out here?

142
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:04,000
And that, of course, is much too hard to measure.

143
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:07,000
That's way, way beyond the ability to measure.

144
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:10,000
But the vacuum energy that's present

145
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:13,000
just in empty space gravitates,

146
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:16,000
and the effect of that gravitation

147
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:18,000
is the accelerated expansion

148
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:20,000
of the universe.

149
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:22,000
So really when people talk about vacuum energy

150
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:25,000
and real, real honest evidence for it,

151
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:27,000
the only real evidence for it

152
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:30,000
is the accelerated expansion of the universe.

153
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:34,000
So that's, I would put it that way.

154
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:37,000
There's other ways to think about

155
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:40,000
the force between these plates here

156
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:42,000
than thinking about vacuum energy.

157
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,000
You can just think about it

158
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:45,000
as the force between plates.

159
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:47,000
Yeah.

160
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:52,000
How can the Casimir force ever be positive?

161
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:54,000
How can it be repulsive?

162
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:58,000
How can the...

163
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:02,000
I think it depends on the kind of particle

164
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:05,000
that's, I think if there are,

165
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:09,000
I believe that if there were fermions

166
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:11,000
which were mediating the force,

167
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:14,000
that it would be positive and not negative.

168
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:16,000
I think that's true.

169
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:18,000
I have to check that, but I think so.

170
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,000
I don't know.

171
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:24,000
Do you have any idea why the popular articles

172
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:26,000
about vacuum energy

173
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:28,000
all call it mysterious

174
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:34,000
and seem to say it's an unknown?

175
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:35,000
Do physicists...

176
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:37,000
Look, I've explained this over and over again.

177
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:42,000
All quantum field theories predict

178
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:44,000
the existence of vacuum energy.

179
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:47,000
Is that mysterious?

180
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:50,000
Well, okay.

181
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:53,000
It's something that's very, very well established

182
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:55,000
