00:50:37,480 --> 00:50:39,480
would create ordinary particles,

1139
00:50:39,480 --> 00:50:41,480
in thermal equilibrium,

1140
00:50:41,480 --> 00:50:44,480
there would be some kind of balance between them.

1141
00:50:44,480 --> 00:50:49,480
So the expectation was,

1142
00:50:49,480 --> 00:50:51,480
I don't know what was going

1143
00:50:51,480 --> 00:50:53,480
on at the very, very beginning,

1144
00:50:53,480 --> 00:50:57,480
but if we trace back as far as we can,

1145
00:50:57,480 --> 00:51:00,480
it looks more like there was

1146
00:51:00,480 --> 00:51:04,480
an equal abundance of these various kinds of things.

1147
00:51:04,480 --> 00:51:05,480
Yeah.

1148
00:51:05,480 --> 00:51:07,480
So the LSP,

1149
00:51:07,480 --> 00:51:11,480
which ordinary particle would that be the partner of?

1150
00:51:11,480 --> 00:51:14,480
It would have to be non-interactive, right?

1151
00:51:14,480 --> 00:51:16,480
Yeah, very likely a neutral,

1152
00:51:16,480 --> 00:51:18,480
almost certainly a neutral particle.

1153
00:51:18,480 --> 00:51:19,480
Why?

1154
00:51:19,480 --> 00:51:22,480
Well, for one reason is that

1155
00:51:22,480 --> 00:51:25,480
a charged particle is likely to be some,

1156
00:51:25,480 --> 00:51:28,480
or a colored particle is likely to be somewhat heavier

1157
00:51:28,480 --> 00:51:29,480
than its neutral,

1158
00:51:29,480 --> 00:51:32,480
than a neutral version of it.

1159
00:51:32,480 --> 00:51:33,480
Why?

1160
00:51:33,480 --> 00:51:36,480
Because of electrostatic or color forces,

1161
00:51:36,480 --> 00:51:39,480
color energy densities.

1162
00:51:39,480 --> 00:51:41,480
So the expectation would be

1163
00:51:41,480 --> 00:51:43,480
that it would be a neutral particle,

1164
00:51:43,480 --> 00:51:46,480
but in various versions of the theory,

1165
00:51:46,480 --> 00:51:48,480
it could be different things.

1166
00:51:48,480 --> 00:51:51,480
It could be the partner of the photon,

1167
00:51:51,480 --> 00:51:53,480
it could be the partner of the Higgs boson,

1168
00:51:53,480 --> 00:51:55,480
it could be the partner of the graviton,

1169
00:51:55,480 --> 00:51:57,480
which is called the gravitino.

1170
00:51:57,480 --> 00:52:03,480
And various different possibilities.

1171
00:52:03,480 --> 00:52:05,480
I don't think there's any definitive idea

1172
00:52:05,480 --> 00:52:09,480
of what the lightest superpartner is.

1173
00:52:09,480 --> 00:52:13,480
What's the difference between the Higgs divergence

1174
00:52:13,480 --> 00:52:15,480
and the vacuum energy divergence?

1175
00:52:15,480 --> 00:52:17,480
Yeah, well, it is different.

1176
00:52:17,480 --> 00:52:20,480
It is different.

1177
00:52:20,480 --> 00:52:22,480
The vacuum energy divergence is just

1178
00:52:22,480 --> 00:52:24,480
the energy of empty space.

1179
00:52:24,480 --> 00:52:26,480
And in terms of Feynman diagram,

1180
00:52:26,480 --> 00:52:33,480
in terms of Feynman diagrams,

1181
00:52:33,480 --> 00:52:36,480
in terms of Feynman diagrams,

1182
00:52:36,480 --> 00:52:39,480
it's just diagrams of virtual particles

1183
00:52:39,480 --> 00:52:41,480
which sort of populate empty space.

1184
00:52:41,480 --> 00:52:43,480
Complicated Feynman diagrams,

1185
00:52:43,480 --> 00:52:46,480
all sorts of Feynman diagrams can take place,

1186
00:52:46,480 --> 00:52:51,480
but they're in otherwise completely empty space,

1187
00:52:51,480 --> 00:52:54,480
and they contribute energy to the vacuum.

1188
00:52:54,480 --> 00:52:56,480
The self-energy of a particle

1189
00:52:56,480 --> 00:52:58,480
in particular the Higgs particle,

1190
00:52:58,480 --> 00:53:01,480
is a class of diagrams

1191
00:53:01,480 --> 00:53:03,480
in which the presence of the...

1192
00:53:03,480 --> 00:53:05,480
Basically you can say it this way,

1193
00:53:05,480 --> 00:53:07,480
the presence of the Higgs particle

1194
00:53:07,480 --> 00:53:09,480
or any other particle

1195
00:53:09,480 --> 00:53:13,480
provides a kind of impurity in the vacuum.

1196
00:53:13,480 --> 00:53:15,480
It's...

1197
00:53:15,480 --> 00:53:17,480
That's what a particle is.

1198
00:53:17,480 --> 00:53:19,480
It's an impurity in the vacuum.

1199
00:53:19,480 --> 00:53:22,480
The impurity has an effect

1200
00:53:22,480 --> 00:53:25,480
on these vacuum diagrams.

1201
00:53:25,480 --> 00:53:27,480
Its presence modifies them

1202
00:53:27,480 --> 00:53:30,480
in a way which is not too different

1203
00:53:30,480 --> 00:53:33,480
than the plates of the Casimir effect.

1204
00:53:33,480 --> 00:53:36,480
But you can summarize it by saying

1205
00:53:36,480 --> 00:53:38,480
the important Feynman diagrams

1206
00:53:38,480 --> 00:53:41,480
for renormalizing or shifting the mass of a particle

1207
00:53:41,480 --> 00:53:43,480
are just diagrams which are connected

1208
00:53:43,480 --> 00:53:46,480
to that particle like that.

1209
00:53:46,480 --> 00:53:49,480
So the Feynman diagrams

1210
00:53:49,480 --> 00:53:51,480
which are sensitive to the presence

1211
00:53:51,480 --> 00:53:53,480
of the Higgs particle

1212
00:53:53,480 --> 00:53:55,480
give a mass to...

1213
00:53:55,480 --> 00:53:57,480
or shift the mass of the Higgs particle

1214
00:53:57,480 --> 00:53:58,480
and that's...

1215
00:53:58,480 --> 00:54:00,480
It is in a sense

1216
00:54:00,480 --> 00:54:02,480
the same kind of phenomena

1217
00:54:02,480 --> 00:54:05,480
except it is...

1218
00:54:05,480 --> 00:54:07,480
What shall we say?

1219
00:54:07,480 --> 00:54:10,480
Modified by the presence of the Higgs particle itself

1220
00:54:10,480 --> 00:54:13,480
and therefore shifts the mass of the Higgs particle

1221
00:54:16,480 --> 00:54:18,480
whereas the vacuum diagrams

1222
00:54:18,480 --> 00:54:20,480
are just shifting the mass

1223
00:54:20,480 --> 00:54:22,480
or the energy density of the empty space.

1224
00:54:23,480 --> 00:54:25,480
There is one thing,

1225
00:54:25,480 --> 00:54:27,480
there is an interesting fact

1226
00:54:27,480 --> 00:54:29,480
which we haven't explored cosmology

1227
00:54:29,480 --> 00:54:31,480
at least for a number of quarters

1228
00:54:31,480 --> 00:54:35,480
but there is one feature

1229
00:54:35,480 --> 00:54:37,480
of this vacuum energy

1230
00:54:37,480 --> 00:54:39,480
which is what distinguishes it

1231
00:54:39,480 --> 00:54:41,480
and makes it rather special.

1232
00:54:41,480 --> 00:54:45,480
Let's talk first about ordinary energy

1233
00:54:45,480 --> 00:54:47,480
stored in the form of particles,

1234
00:54:47,480 --> 00:54:49,480
lots of particles.

1235
00:54:49,480 --> 00:54:51,480
They could be dark matter particles,

1236
00:54:51,480 --> 00:54:53,480
they could be any kind of particles.

1237
00:54:53,480 --> 00:54:55,480
Eventually at some point

1238
00:54:55,480 --> 00:54:57,480
as the universe expands

1239
00:54:57,480 --> 00:54:59,480
these particles separate enough

1240
00:54:59,480 --> 00:55:01,480
that they are not in violent interaction

1241
00:55:01,480 --> 00:55:03,480
with each other.

1242
00:55:03,480 --> 00:55:05,480
They are just more or less sitting there

1243
00:55:05,480 --> 00:55:07,480
and as the universe expands

1244
00:55:07,480 --> 00:55:09,480
they separate.

1245
00:55:09,480 --> 00:55:11,480
And as they separate

1246
00:55:11,480 --> 00:55:13,480
the energy density decreases.

1247
00:55:13,480 --> 00:55:15,480
The energy density decreases

1248
00:55:15,480 --> 00:55:17,480
because the volume of space increases

1249
00:55:17,480 --> 00:55:19,480
the number of particles doesn't increase

1250
00:55:19,480 --> 00:55:21,480
and the result is

1251
00:55:21,480 --> 00:55:23,480
that the energy density of the vacuum

1252
00:55:23,480 --> 00:55:25,480
sorry, the energy density of space

1253
00:55:25,480 --> 00:55:27,480
due to ordinary particles

1254
00:55:27,480 --> 00:55:33,480
decreases as the universe expands.

1255
00:55:33,480 --> 00:55:35,480
It works differently for photons

1256
00:55:35,480 --> 00:55:37,480
than for particles with mass.

1257
00:55:37,480 --> 00:55:39,480
The reason is the following.

1258
00:55:39,480 --> 00:55:41,480
The particles with mass

1259
00:55:41,480 --> 00:55:43,480
due to the expansion of the universe

1260
00:55:43,480 --> 00:55:45,480
eventually come to rest

1261
00:55:45,480 --> 00:55:47,480
relative to each other.

1262
00:55:47,480 --> 00:55:49,480
No, they don't come to rest

1263
00:55:49,480 --> 00:55:51,480
relative to each other.

1264
00:55:51,480 --> 00:55:53,480
They just participate in the overall

1265
00:55:53,480 --> 00:55:55,480
expansion.

1266
00:55:55,480 --> 00:55:59,480
But think of them as roughly being at rest

1267
00:55:59,480 --> 00:56:01,480
in a local frame over here.

1268
00:56:01,480 --> 00:56:03,480
Their energy is just mc squared.

1269
00:56:03,480 --> 00:56:05,480
Or their mass is just

1270
00:56:05,480 --> 00:56:07,480
their mass is just their mass

1271
00:56:07,480 --> 00:56:09,480
and the way you find the energy density

1272
00:56:09,480 --> 00:56:11,480
or the mass in a certain region

1273
00:56:11,480 --> 00:56:13,480
is just to add up all the particles

1274
00:56:13,480 --> 00:56:15,480
and give each one a mass m.

1275
00:56:15,480 --> 00:56:17,480
Okay?

1276
00:56:17,480 --> 00:56:19,480
That's the way you would calculate

1277
00:56:19,480 --> 00:56:21,480
the energy of just ordinary particles.

1278
00:56:21,480 --> 00:56:23,480
You just take all the particles

1279
00:56:23,480 --> 00:56:25,480
and then divide it by that volume

1280
00:56:25,480 --> 00:56:27,480
that's the energy density

1281
00:56:27,480 --> 00:56:29,480
and then as the volume expands

1282
00:56:29,480 --> 00:56:31,480
the particles just move out

1283
00:56:31,480 --> 00:56:33,480
with the expanding volume

1284
00:56:33,480 --> 00:56:35,480
they just participate in the expansion

1285
00:56:35,480 --> 00:56:37,480
and the energy density decreases

1286
00:56:37,480 --> 00:56:39,480
but the total amount of energy

1287
00:56:39,480 --> 00:56:41,480
in a volume like this stays fixed.

1288
00:56:41,480 --> 00:56:43,480
Okay?

1289
00:56:43,480 --> 00:56:45,480
Another example would be

1290
00:56:45,480 --> 00:56:47,480
a volume of space with photons in it.

1291
00:56:49,480 --> 00:56:51,480
Photons in it.

1292
00:56:51,480 --> 00:56:53,480
You can think

1293
00:56:53,480 --> 00:56:55,480
qualitatively of just having

1294
00:56:55,480 --> 00:56:57,480
a cavity with photons in it.

1295
00:56:57,480 --> 00:56:59,480
Of course in reality the photons

1296
00:56:59,480 --> 00:57:01,480
pass out through the walls of this region

1297
00:57:01,480 --> 00:57:03,480
freely. There are no real walls.

1298
00:57:03,480 --> 00:57:05,480
But for every photon that passes out

1299
00:57:05,480 --> 00:57:07,480
there's also likely to be another one

1300
00:57:07,480 --> 00:57:09,480
coming in.

1301
00:57:09,480 --> 00:57:11,480
So you can imagine a region of space

1302
00:57:11,480 --> 00:57:13,480
an expanding region of space

1303
00:57:13,480 --> 00:57:15,480
an expanding region of space

1304
00:57:15,480 --> 00:57:17,480
where the number of photons

1305
00:57:17,480 --> 00:57:19,480
stays fixed.

1306
00:57:19,480 --> 00:57:21,480
But each photon

1307
00:57:21,480 --> 00:57:23,480
each wave of space

1308
00:57:23,480 --> 00:57:25,480
each wave in here gets stretched

1309
00:57:25,480 --> 00:57:27,480
by the expansion

1310
00:57:27,480 --> 00:57:29,480
its wavelength gets stretched

1311
00:57:29,480 --> 00:57:31,480
and so as its wavelength gets stretched

1312
00:57:31,480 --> 00:57:33,480
the corresponding energy

1313
00:57:33,480 --> 00:57:35,480
of each photon decreases.

1314
00:57:35,480 --> 00:57:37,480
So that means

1315
00:57:37,480 --> 00:57:39,480
relative to the massive particles

1316
00:57:39,480 --> 00:57:41,480
this is called just

1317
00:57:41,480 --> 00:57:43,480
non-relativistic massive particles

1318
00:57:43,480 --> 00:57:45,480
the energy density

1319
00:57:45,480 --> 00:57:47,480
stored in radiation

1320
00:57:47,480 --> 00:57:49,480
will decrease faster

1321
00:57:49,480 --> 00:57:51,480
as the universe expands

1322
00:57:51,480 --> 00:57:53,480
than the energy density

1323
00:57:53,480 --> 00:57:55,480
stored in ordinary particles.

1324
00:57:55,480 --> 00:57:57,480
This is why today

1325
00:57:57,480 --> 00:57:59,480
the energy density in radiation

1326
00:57:59,480 --> 00:58:01,480
black body radiation

1327
00:58:01,480 --> 00:58:03,480
is vastly smaller

1328
00:58:03,480 --> 00:58:05,480
than the energy density in protons

1329
00:58:05,480 --> 00:58:07,480
nuclei

1330
00:58:07,480 --> 00:58:09,480
and electrons and so forth

1331
00:58:09,480 --> 00:58:11,480
because the expansion

1332
00:58:11,480 --> 00:58:13,480
has stretched the photons

1333
00:58:13,480 --> 00:58:15,480
but it hasn't changed the mass of the particles here.

1334
00:58:15,480 --> 00:58:17,480
If you go back into the past

1335
00:58:17,480 --> 00:58:19,480
at one point the energy densities

1336
